



Sir
Prince William County May 16th 1758



In Obedience to His Honr The Presidents orders to me wch I inclose you a Copy off.1 I have Sent One hundred Men of
[185]
this Militia Commanded by Capt. Thos McClanahan & Capt. William Tebbs to Garrison Fort Loudoun at Winchester.2
I have directed them to Apply to you for Arms & Ammunition & to the Commissary for Provisions: the arms sent for the Use of this County Not being yet Arrived.3 I am Sir Your Most Obedient Hble Servt

Henry Lee

